attributes.magic: PE32+ executable (GUI) x86-64 (stripped to external PDB), for MS Windows

exiftool.ImageFileCharacteristics: No relocs, Executable, No line numbers, No symbols, Large address aware, No debug

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The sample exhibits definitive characteristics of a malware stager or loader. It utilizes a routine (sub_401595) that allocates memory via VirtualAlloc, performs an XOR-based decryption of a payload, manually resolves critical APIs (GetModuleHandleA, GetProcAddress) into the payload buffer (sub_401563), transitions memory protection to PAGE_EXECUTE_READ via VirtualProtect, and executes the resulting shellcode using CreateThread. Additionally, the binary implements inter-process communication through a named pipe using the pattern '\\.\pipe\p-i-p-e\MSSE-%d-server', a behavior commonly associated with post-exploitation frameworks and lateral movement.
